problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in physics would. What is the SMILES expression of (1S,2R)-N-ethyl-2-pyrrolidin-1-ylcycloheptan-1-amine?
Answer:
gpt_response: The SMILES expression of (1S,2R)-N-ethyl-2-pyrrolidin-1-ylcycloheptan-1-amine is CCN1CCCC2C1CCCCC2N(C)C. SMILES (Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry System) notation is a way of representing the structure of a molecule using a simple and concise string of characters. In this case, the notation indicates the connectivity of the atoms in the molecule and the types of bonds between them.
